    "title": "Sync Interrupted, Can't continue synching full node.",
    "body": "Was synching my full node for 4 days now, got to block 350K until we had a power outage. Right now, I can't start bitcoind, getting a permission error and also getting a permission error in the debug.log file.\r\n\r\nWhen I try to run bitcoind -daemon..\r\nError: Cannot write to data directory '/home/pi/.bitcoin'; check permissions.\r\n\r\nTail of debug.log file..\r\n\r\n2018-07-04T23:27:33Z *** System error while flushing: Fatal LevelDB error: IO error: /home/pi/.bitcoin/blocks/index/000324.log: Read-only file system\r\n2018-07-04T23:27:33Z Error: Error: A fatal internal error occurred, see debug.log for details\r\n2018-07-04T23:27:33Z FlushStateToDisk: failed to flush state (System error while flushing: Fatal LevelDB error: IO error: /home/pi/.bitcoin/blocks/index/000324.log: Read-only file system (code 0))\r\n\r\nAny help or advice would be greatly appreciated!\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\nArmin",
