      "body": "I have remounted the drive using \"sudo mount -o remount,rw /dev/sdb2\".\r\nI have also ran bitcoind -reindex. \r\n\r\nIt continues to crash after a while.\r\n\r\nHere is the output of the db.log file:\r\n\r\nwallet.dat: unable to flush: Read-only file system\r\nwallet.dat: unable to flush: Read-only file system\r\nwallet.dat: unable to flush: Read-only file system\r\ntxn_checkpoint: failed to flush the buffer cache: Read-only file system\r\nwallet.dat: Read-only file system\r\n\r\nI've tried this a few times now, but Bitcoin Core continues to crash for me.\r\n\r\n",
